s – including Fitzgerald, Moore, O’Neill, Steinbeck and Stevens – it makes for essential reading for students and academics working on twentieth-century American and Irish literature and culture, and transatlantic studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAmerican literature.  aCeltic Revival.  aIrish literature.  aW. B. Yeats.  ainfluence.  amodernism.  apolitics.  atransatlantic studies.1 aStubbs, Tara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610227040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526102270423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526102270/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles